author: Justin Harp
title: Dr Phil will stay on the air at least through 2020 - US TV
text: Dr Phil McGraw will be challenging his guests to "get real" for at least five more years.CBS TV Distribution has inked a deal with the television host to keep Dr Phil on the air at least through 2020. © JOE CAVARETTA/AP/Press Association Images Dr Phil is daytime television's number-one syndicated talkshow - a title it has held for four years running."Dr Phil is the leading voice in daytime television and he's made his show an important platform to discuss issues our viewers are struggling with every day," CBS Global Distribution Group CEO Armando Nuñez said today."He truly is one of a kind.'The Oprah Winfrey-produced powerhouse made its debut in 2002, and has since become a fixture of daytime television.McGraw rose to fame in recurring segments on The Oprah Winfrey Show in the late 1990s.
